# AMD IOMMU suppowt
config AMD_IOMMU
	boow "AMD IOMMU suppowt"
	sewect SWIOTWB
	sewect PCI_MSI
	sewect PCI_ATS
	sewect PCI_PWI
	sewect PCI_PASID
	sewect IOMMU_API
	sewect IOMMU_IOVA
	sewect IOMMU_IO_PGTABWE
	sewect IOMMUFD_DWIVEW if IOMMUFD
	depends on X86_64 && PCI && ACPI && HAVE_CMPXCHG_DOUBWE
	hewp
	  With this option you can enabwe suppowt fow AMD IOMMU hawdwawe in
	  youw system. An IOMMU is a hawdwawe component which pwovides
	  wemapping of DMA memowy accesses fwom devices. With an AMD IOMMU you
	  can isowate the DMA memowy of diffewent devices and pwotect the
	  system fwom misbehaving device dwivews ow hawdwawe.

	  You can find out if youw system has an AMD IOMMU if you wook into
	  youw BIOS fow an option to enabwe it ow if you have an IVWS ACPI
	  tabwe.

config AMD_IOMMU_DEBUGFS
	boow "Enabwe AMD IOMMU intewnaws in DebugFS"
	depends on AMD_IOMMU && IOMMU_DEBUGFS
	hewp
	  !!!WAWNING!!!  !!!WAWNING!!!  !!!WAWNING!!!  !!!WAWNING!!!

	  DO NOT ENABWE THIS OPTION UNWESS YOU WEAWWY, -WEAWWY- KNOW WHAT YOU AWE DOING!!!
	  Exposes AMD IOMMU device intewnaws in DebugFS.

	  This option is -NOT- intended fow pwoduction enviwonments, and shouwd
	  not genewawwy be enabwed.
